# .argotignore — layered on top of argot:recommended.
# argot:recommended already skips docs/, benchmarks/, build/ and *.test.ts /
# *.config.ts files, so hono's docs/, benchmarks/, build/ and co-located
# *.test.ts specs need no entry here. These are the hono-specific dirs
# argot:recommended does NOT cover, and that shouldn't shape the library's voice:

# Cross-runtime integration test harnesses (bun/deno/node/workerd/lambda/…).
# The *.test.ts files are already dropped, but the harness code (mock.ts,
# stream-mock.ts, index.ts, vitest configs) is test scaffolding, not library voice.
runtime-tests/

# Performance-measurement tooling and scripts (bundle-size / type-check probes).
# Dev tooling that ships nothing — not how the core library is written.
perf-measures/
